20:36.610 --> 20:39.675
because they still remembered that he was a foreigner, he wasn't even a Babylonian, he was a Jew.

20:41.898 --> 20:43.160
He had enemies around him.

20:44.222 --> 20:45.043
We have enemies.

20:45.824 --> 20:47.767
I'm not talking about people out there on the street.

20:48.167 --> 20:53.916
Yes, we might have people who we strongly disagree with or people disagree with us, but we have an enemy.

20:55.438 --> 21:03.090
Scriptures tell us that there is an enemy of our souls who goes about as a roaring lion, he goes about spreading fear,

21:03.426 --> 21:06.870
spreading distrust, spreading lies, spreading deceit.

21:08.852 --> 21:14.458
And as the people of God, often we are His targets, especially if we are walking in the purposes of God.

21:15.099 --> 21:21.226
The enemy's out there stirring up things against us, stirring up people against us, creating troubles for us.

21:22.728 --> 21:28.374
Daniel had these enemies and they plotted against them and they passed the law.

21:28.414 --> 21:32.018
They talked the Darius into passing a law that banned

21:33.026 --> 21:37.470
prayer or petition to any other being other than the king.

21:38.472 --> 21:40.353
You can read it in Daniel chapter six.

21:40.894 --> 21:43.857
And they passed the law to bound it.

21:44.878 --> 21:53.427
And Daniel heard of this and Daniel chapter six and verse number 10, it says, now when Daniel knew that the writing was signed, he went home.

21:54.428 --> 22:00.754
And in his upper room with his window open towards Jerusalem, he knelt down on his knees three times a day

22:00.898 --> 22:06.543
and prayed and give thanks before his God as was his custom since early days.

22:07.204 --> 22:07.985
Praise the Lord.

22:09.146 --> 22:09.907
Praise the Lord.

22:10.407 --> 22:11.628
You know, that gets me excited.

22:12.789 --> 22:13.850
That gets me excited.

22:13.890 --> 22:16.113
He heard of the troubles.

22:17.154 --> 22:28.264
He heard that there was a threat on his life, maybe not his personal, but he knew that if anyone petitioned anyone other than Darius, that there was a threat in their lives, they were going to the lion's den.

22:28.705 --> 22:30.226
He knew that there was a threat,

22:31.010 --> 22:31.771
I was hanging over them.

22:32.913 --> 22:38.702
He could have said, I'm going to fast prayer for Lent and everything would have been okay.

22:39.703 --> 22:52.082
He could have said, you know what, maybe I'll just skip it for a wee while and I'll focus just on the word, which is not a bad thing to focus on the word, but he says, no, I've got a window to go to.

22:53.224 --> 22:54.887
I've got a window I need to go to.

22:55.107 --> 22:55.888
No, it wasn't the window.

22:55.928 --> 22:57.010
The window is irrelevant.

22:57.314 --> 23:01.801
The point was that he had a relationship with God and the windows symbolized that relationship with God.

23:02.663 --> 23:05.908
And he said, I'm not going to let these troubles overwhelm me.

23:06.509 --> 23:12.919
The threat of violence, the threat of danger, just as Elijah had a threat from the king, from the queen.

23:12.979 --> 23:15.804
Here Daniel's got a threat from the king.

23:15.824 --> 23:18.047
He said, it's in his laws.

23:19.890 --> 23:22.354
Daniel said, no, I'm not going to let that happen.

23:23.298 --> 23:27.864
He had a window, but more importantly, he had a place in his heart that was not troubled.

23:29.105 --> 23:31.088
He wasn't moved by what he heard.

23:31.188 --> 23:35.193
He wasn't moved by the troubles that were coming against him, by the threats.

23:36.314 --> 23:40.339
He would not allow his troubles to dictate his relationship with God.

23:41.360 --> 23:45.005
He would not allow his troubles to prevent him from going on with God.

23:47.708 --> 23:49.490
That's an important lesson for us, isn't it?

23:51.426 --> 23:58.236
Don't let what we're going through today, good or bad, affect us going on with God tomorrow.

23:59.619 --> 24:02.383
Don't make this a full stop in your life.

24:02.403 --> 24:08.953
Don't make this struggle, this trial, this trouble that you're in, become a full stop to your Christian walk with God.

24:14.381 --> 24:17.045
Because it's not a sin to be troubled.

24:18.808 --> 24:20.050
It's not a sin to be

24:20.322 --> 24:21.864
overwhelmed at times.

24:21.924 --> 24:24.348
It's not a sin to question or to doubt.

24:25.450 --> 24:26.431
It's what you do with it.

24:27.292 --> 24:28.294
Do you dwell upon it?

24:29.335 --> 24:30.717
Do you get stuck in that moment?

24:31.498 --> 24:33.762
Do you become like Elijah and become catatonic?

24:33.802 --> 24:35.144
And just that's it.

24:35.785 --> 24:36.806
I'm not going to go any further.

24:39.370 --> 24:40.612
See, God wants you to move on.

24:40.692 --> 24:41.553
He wants you to grow.

24:41.593 --> 24:45.960
He wants us to remain in His purposes and His plans for our life.

24:46.440 --> 24:46.741
Lives.

24:47.422 --> 24:48.864
He wants us to do well.

24:48.904 --> 24:50.226
He wants us to succeed.

24:50.818 --> 24:51.559
The enemy doesn't.

24:52.901 --> 24:53.962
The enemy wants you to stop.

24:55.064 --> 25:01.173
The enemy wants you to camp at this disaster, at this dread, at this trouble, and go no further.

25:03.175 --> 25:04.598
But God wants you to go on with that.

25:05.919 --> 25:16.274
Elijah remained in that place, discouragement, disappointment with the God, disappointment with his followers, disappointment with the leaders of the nation.

25:18.178 --> 25:25.089
Daniel refused to remain in the place of trouble and said he went to his window where he met with God Almighty.

25:25.550 --> 25:26.671
Praise the Lord.

25:27.272 --> 25:28.875
Glory to God in heaven.

25:29.456 --> 25:30.538
Praise the Lord.

25:31.719 --> 25:32.501
That's wonderful.

25:34.304 --> 25:35.425
It's wonderful news.

25:35.485 --> 25:41.815
It's wonderful inspiration for us, encouragement for us to keep going, to keep on moving on.

25:45.020 --> 25:46.002
Jesus was troubled.

25:48.002 --> 25:49.424
by what he was going to face.

25:50.906 --> 25:58.217
He struggled with it, but he did not allow that trouble to stop him from accomplishing the father's plan.

25:59.739 --> 26:01.622
He didn't let that trouble overwhelm him.

26:02.984 --> 26:06.750
He says he said his face is a flint and he went, I'm doing it.

26:07.751 --> 26:09.353
Doesn't mean he wasn't troubled because he was.

26:10.375 --> 26:13.940
He tells us that in John 13, but he went ahead.

26:14.000 --> 26:17.906
He didn't let the trouble stop him from going forward.

26:19.970 --> 26:25.959
The second part of our verse this morning is in John 14, one is, you believe in God, believe also in me.

26:26.640 --> 26:30.046
Let not your heart be troubled, you believe in God, believe also in me.

26:32.249 --> 26:34.933
This is not a suggestion by Jesus.

26:35.614 --> 26:45.970
He's giving advice for how to get out of that moment of trouble, out of that step, out of that stuck in that moment, out of that trouble, how to get past that,

26:49.570 --> 26:51.973
Jesus is saying, you believe in God, believe in me.

26:52.994 --> 27:00.202
With the same manner in which you believe, trust and have faith in God, have that same level of belief, trust and faith in Jesus.

27:02.044 --> 27:02.404
You know what?

27:02.444 --> 27:04.226
It's easier for us to say that now.

27:04.246 --> 27:05.548
It really is.

27:06.269 --> 27:09.673
When you think about it, as far as Abraham concerned, he was a Messiah.

27:10.453 --> 27:18.162
They didn't have a full understanding or revelation that he was a third person of the Trinity, the Son of God, divine himself,

27:19.586 --> 27:22.250
We have such a greater understanding of who he is.

27:24.452 --> 27:26.375
What he says here is, you believe in Theos.

27:27.036 --> 27:32.443
God is Theos, which is a supreme divine ruler and judge of all the universe.

27:33.765 --> 27:34.806
This is who you believe in.

27:36.068 --> 27:37.450
Believe in me also.

27:38.571 --> 27:45.541
The one sent by God, not only to teach, but to bring good news, who actually is the good news.

27:46.622 --> 27:49.586
The one who is here to redeem and to save you.

27:49.954 --> 27:50.695
He's a good news.

27:50.735 --> 27:51.456
Believe in him.

27:51.476 --> 27:55.781
Have as much confidence in him as you have in God.

27:58.183 --> 28:18.386
He tells him, this clause, Dr. Dutteridge interprets this clause and he says, believe in God, the Almighty guardian of his servants, faithful servants, who has made such glorious promises to prosper and succeed, the cause in which you are engaged.

28:19.778 --> 28:32.296
Believe in God the Almighty Guardian of His faithful servants who has made such glorious promises to prosper and succeed the cause in which you are engaged and believe also in me.

28:32.336 --> 28:43.191
As a promised Messiah who, whether present or absent in body, shall always be mindful of your concerns as well as ever able to help you.

28:44.193 --> 28:44.994
Glory to God.

28:46.876 --> 28:48.018
What a Savior.

28:48.994 --> 28:50.276
What a savior.

28:51.497 --> 28:55.102
Scriptures tell us that right now he ever lives to make intercession for us.

28:56.484 --> 28:57.485
He's thinking of us.

28:58.687 --> 29:01.871
In that moment of panic or fear of dread, he's praying for us.

29:02.692 --> 29:03.753
Remember his words to Peter?

29:03.793 --> 29:10.582
Peter, Peter, the enemy wants to sift you as wheat, but I pray that your faith feel us not.

29:12.365 --> 29:13.426
He's praying for us.

29:14.082 --> 29:15.344
He wants us to succeed.

29:15.384 --> 29:22.456
He wants us to move forward, to grow, to rise up as men and women of God, to be all that He has called us to be.

29:22.496 --> 29:29.808
It's important that we remind ourselves of that.

29:33.654 --> 29:34.676
And we have hope in Him.

29:35.918 --> 29:38.482
It's important that we have hope in Him and who He is.

29:44.450 --> 29:47.914
Alexander McLaren, talking about the same verse.

29:49.275 --> 29:58.645
He said, the 12 were sitting in the upper chamber, stupefied with the dreary, half understood prospect of Christ's departure.

29:59.767 --> 30:04.472
He, forgetting his own burden, turns to comfort and encourage them.

30:05.313 --> 30:09.537
These sweet and great words most singularly blend gentleness and dignity.

30:10.619 --> 30:13.842
Who can reproduce the condense of soothing tenderness?

30:14.242 --> 30:18.709
Soft as a mother's hand in that, let not your heart be troubled.

30:19.810 --> 30:26.721
And who can feel to feel the tone of majesty in that, believe in God, believe also in me?

30:30.387 --> 30:31.669
What a wonderful savior.

30:33.992 --> 30:37.177
He spoke to his disciples in that moment when they were struggling.

30:37.838 --> 30:40.562
When they were about to go into the passion week

30:40.834 --> 30:45.421
Christ was gonna go through what he was gonna go through, but they were gonna face their own problems.

30:45.881 --> 30:47.944
They were gonna face their own strife and struggles.

30:50.247 --> 30:53.232
And he said, let not your heart be troubled.

30:53.973 --> 30:55.875
You believe in God, believe also in me.

30:57.478 --> 30:59.020
And that's a word to us today, isn't it?

31:00.322 --> 31:05.289
Wherever you are and whatever you're going through today, let me say to you, let not your heart be troubled.

31:06.190 --> 31:08.914
You believe in God, believe also in Jesus.

31:10.690 --> 31:11.932
No problem is so big.

31:11.952 --> 31:14.835
No mountain is so great that Jesus can't help you.

31:16.838 --> 31:19.401
He is a God of all the universe.

31:19.521 --> 31:20.082
He loves us.

31:20.543 --> 31:21.264
He died for us.

31:21.324 --> 31:23.807
He's a better price for us.

31:23.827 --> 31:26.530
I've gone through things in my life and those words have come back to me.

31:27.291 --> 31:29.594
He didn't build his home in me to move away.

31:30.275 --> 31:32.057
He didn't teach me to swim to let me drown.

31:33.419 --> 31:36.163
And that's wonderful truth in that, isn't it?

31:36.183 --> 31:37.224
That he is invested in you.

31:37.244 --> 31:38.866
He wants you to see you succeed.

31:39.202 --> 31:45.611
He wants to see you get past your troubles, maybe even just insulate you from the troubles.

31:45.631 --> 31:48.114
Don't let them become overwhelming in your heart.

31:49.496 --> 31:54.302
He loves you and he wants to see you rising up as a man and woman of God.

31:54.903 --> 32:02.814
He doesn't want to see you catatonic like Elijah in the wilderness, doing nothing, struggling, a full stop at your life.

32:03.174 --> 32:04.195
He doesn't want that at all.

32:04.676 --> 32:06.098
He wants your story to continue.

32:06.338 --> 32:09.563
He wants you to move on and to grow in grace and in the knowledge of God.

32:15.313 --> 32:16.935
Lord God in heaven we praise you.

32:18.658 --> 32:21.042
Lord we just take a moment and we praise you.

32:21.663 --> 32:23.426
We thank you that you're our God.

32:23.867 --> 32:26.331
We thank you Lord in heaven that you know us.

32:27.413 --> 32:28.535
You know what we're like.

32:29.877 --> 32:33.042
You know how our minds work and how our hearts work.

32:34.242 --> 32:36.725
You know how we can struggle with things of this world?

32:37.366 --> 32:41.911
You know how we can struggle when we sometimes hear from a doctor or a bad report?

32:43.152 --> 32:46.376
You know how we struggle when we hear people who speak against us?

32:47.037 --> 32:50.821
When we have things happen in our lives, when we have things happen in our households?

32:51.502 --> 32:53.945
You know how those things become major to us?

32:54.385 --> 32:56.488
And how important they are to us, really, Lord?

32:58.290 --> 33:02.034
But we thank you, dear God, in heaven that you are greater than all our problems.

33:03.074 --> 33:21.543
We thank you, dear God, in heaven, that we can turn to you in our needs, Lord, that we can turn to you, Lord, in our trouble, that we can turn to you, Lord, in our distress, knowing that you are our God, knowing that your ear is ever open unto our cry, knowing that you love us.

33:23.927 --> 33:25.389
Lord, we praise you this morning.

33:26.912 --> 33:28.194
We thank you for your word.

33:29.075 --> 33:30.898
We thank you for your encouragement.

33:31.618 --> 33:33.827
We thank you that you are God and you love us.

33:34.771 --> 33:37.823
Lord, we turn to you and we say that we love you.

33:38.726 --> 33:42.401
And we thank you Lord for who you are.

33:42.542 --> 33:42.642
Amen.

